author: Reuters Editorial
title: Norwegian salmon export price fell to NOK 71.50 last week -SSB
text:
OSLO, April 11 (Reuters) - The export price of fresh farmed Norwegian salmon fell to 71.50 Norwegian crowns ($9.17) per kilo last week from 71.75 crowns the previous week, Statistics Norway said on Wednesday.
Volumes exported rose to 13,953 tonnes from 11,423 tonnes over the same period, it added.
Norway is the world’s largest producer of farmed salmon. The sector is the Nordic country’s second-largest export industry after oil and gas production.
Leading Norwegian producers include Marine Harvest, Salmar, Leroy Seafood, Grieg Seafood , Austevoll Seafood and Norway Royal Salmon . ($1 = 7.7936 Norwegian crowns) (Reporting by Oslo newsroom)
